128
00:06:54,502 --> 00:06:56,932
So what's the breaking news 
in the hen house?

129
00:06:56,932 --> 00:06:59,989
"Dear Lo, in a real pickle here.

130
00:06:59,989 --> 00:07:04,494
Will a polka-dot frock, or a flower-print  
dress turn my Jack's head?"

131
00:07:04,494 --> 00:07:07,605
"Dear In A Pickle:  
You want to turn your Jack's head,

132
00:07:07,605 --> 00:07:11,354
say 'boo' to the frock  
and show him the birthday suit."

133
00:07:11,354 --> 00:07:14,742
That gal's asking you  
a serious question, Lo.

134
00:07:14,742 --> 00:07:18,497
Serious? What Truman's going 
to do about the Japanese, that serious.

135
00:07:18,497 --> 00:07:20,916
Women don't want to be  
bothered with war talk.

136
00:07:20,916 --> 00:07:25,269
Cause meat pies and nylons are 
so much more interesting.

137
00:07:25,269 --> 00:07:26,913
Hi, Miss Russell.

138
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:30,834
Got that newlywed survey going to, uh... 
Martha Body on Spruce?

139
00:07:30,834 --> 00:07:34,360
Think that last paragraph's too much, Lo?

140
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,027
Hmm. Kind of a laugh.

141
00:07:36,027 --> 00:07:39,057
You giving romantic advice.

142
00:07:39,057 --> 00:07:41,416
Oh, really? Why's that?

143
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:42,999
What do you know about it?

144
00:07:42,999 --> 00:07:45,940
- You're a childless old maid. 
- Take a powder, Helen.

145
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:49,693
Women all over this city live 
by the advice in "Dear Lo."

146
00:07:49,693 --> 00:07:51,199
Well, they shouldn't.

147
00:07:51,199 --> 00:07:55,152
Women's page is good for  
wrapping fish, and nothing more.

148
00:07:55,152 --> 00:07:58,278
You blow in, steal my job,

149
00:07:58,278 --> 00:08:00,546
then act like you've got 
something better to do?

150
00:08:00,546 --> 00:08:04,133
- Your job?  
- I should have gotten that column!

151
00:08:06,472 --> 00:08:08,455
I know what women care about.

152
00:08:08,455 --> 00:08:13,503
Soon as McDuff gives me a real 
beat the "Dear Lo" column is all yours.

153
00:08:13,503 --> 00:08:15,354
All fixed up, Birdie.

154
