 ♪ ... to the affirmative

155
00:08:23,028 --> 00:08:25,147
Those two fought like alley cats.

156
00:08:25,147 --> 00:08:28,087
And Helen had some toys in the attic?

157
00:08:28,087 --> 00:08:30,567
Had some crack-ups over the years.

158
00:08:30,567 --> 00:08:32,481
She spent time in mental hospitals.

159
00:08:32,481 --> 00:08:34,915
Was she loopy enough to try and hurt Lo?

160
00:08:34,915 --> 00:08:38,036
- She did benefit from her dying. 
- Yeah? How?

161
00:08:38,036 --> 00:08:41,295
With Lo gone, Helen got that column.

162
00:08:41,295 --> 00:08:44,169
She's still writing it.

163
00:08:52,246 --> 00:08:54,294
So you took over Lo's column.

164
00:08:54,294 --> 00:08:57,572
Changed "Dear Lo" to "Hey, Helen,"  
and the rest is history.

165
00:08:57,572 --> 00:08:59,826
We hear you had a few 
bumps along the way.

166
00:08:59,826 --> 00:09:02,861
- An altercation on a city bus... 
- Misunderstanding.

167
00:09:02,861 --> 00:09:04,947
Hospital stay after disrupting a wedding.

168
00:09:04,947 --> 00:09:08,034
Locked the bride in the choir room,  
and walked down the aisle yourself?

169
00:09:08,034 --> 00:09:10,016
She wasn't really right for him.

170
00:09:10,016 --> 00:09:14,698
We were wondering if, in one of these  
colorful periods, you did something to Lo.

171
00:09:14,698 --> 00:09:17,845
- Like shove her in front of a train? 
- Like that, yeah.

172
00:09:17,845 --> 00:09:21,424
We know you wanted  
that column pretty bad.

173
00:09:21,424 --> 00:09:23,387
You girls are lucky.

174
00:09:23,387 --> 00:09:25,619
You have no idea what it's like  
with a ceiling

175
00:09:25,619 --> 00:09:27,780
above you, 
blocking how far you can rise.

176
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:29,787
Not much room for women at the paper?

177
00:09:29,787 --> 00:09:31,956
Hardly room for one, much less two.

178
00:09:31,956 --> 00:09:35,099
So far you to succeed,  
Lo had to go.

179
00:09:35,099 --> 00:09:37,864
Look, I'm a crazy old broad, I admit it,

180
00:09:37,864 --> 00:09:42,436
but Lo was making enemies more  
dangerous than me. / How's that?

181
00:09:42,436 --> 00:09:45,930
She was offering some pretty 
progressive advice in that column.

182
00:09:45,930 --> 00:09:47,802
- And that got her in trouble? 
- Sure did.

183
00:09:47,802 --> 00:09:53,816
The hen house became a hornets' nest  
after some of her ideas hit the street.

184
00:09:57,688 --> 00:09:59,166
Lo Kinney?

185
00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:00,942
That's me.

186
00:10:00,942 --> 00:10:03,326
Hey, where do you get off telling my wife to,

187
00:10:03,326 --> 00:10:05,746
"Beat feet if your dogface  
came home from the war

188
00:10:05,746 --> 00:10:09,239
more interested in his buddies  
than his bride."

189
00:10:11,784 --> 00:10:13,286
I gave that advice to a girl

190
00:10:13,286 --> 00:10:15,857
who wrote in saying her husband  
stopped coming home nights...

191
00:10:15,857 --> 00:10:18,428
and when he did, he was always stinking'. 
That's where.

192
00:10:18,428 --> 00:10:20,942
Man can't come home from the front  
and blow off a little steam...is that it?

193
00:10:20,942 --> 00:10:22,726
Now when he's got a family to think of.

194
00:10:22,726 --> 00:10:26,438
Carousing, blowing your service benefits,  
liquoring up?

195
00:10:26,438 --> 00:10:30,627
The 52-20 Club is for layabouts, mister, 
and it's making your wife nutso with worry.

196
00:10:30,627 --> 00:10:34,395
You got no idea about my life,  
what I been through.

197
00:10:34,395 --> 00:10:35,936
I know what your wife wrote.

198
00:10:35,936 --> 00:10:37,896
And you think that's worth 
throwing away what we got?

199
00:10:37,896 --> 00:10:40,235
For crying out loud, lady!

200
00:10:40,235 --> 00:10:42,610
You married?

201
00:10:42,610 --> 00:10:44,579
Haven't had time, haven't missed it.

202
00:10:44,579 --> 00:10:46,571
So you don't really know 
what you're talking about,

203
00:10:46,571 --> 00:10:49,488
having been left on the shelf 
past expiration yourself.

204
00:10:49,488 --> 00:10:53,328
- She is over 30. 
- Shut your pie hole, Helen.

205
00:10:53,328 --> 00:10:55,888
And you sure as heck 
ain't never been to war.

206
00:10:55,888 --> 00:11:00,224
Wives and soldiers don't have 
any lock on common sense.

207
00:11:00,758 --> 00:11:02,384
I ought to put a crimp in you.

208
00:11:02,384 --> 00:11:05,972
- You're not the first one to threaten it. 
- Yeah, well...

209
00:11:05,972 --> 00:11:08,973
maybe I'll be the last.

210
00:11:15,308 --> 00:11:18,593
I enjoyed it. I did.

211
00:11:18,593 --> 00:11:22,509
Especially that "left on the shelf" business.

212
00:11:22,509 --> 00:11:24,911
Did Lo get a lot of angry visitors?

213
00:11:24,911 --> 00:11:29,342
And she usually mouthed 
right back, but this one rattled her.

214
00:11:29,342 --> 00:11:31,575
Seemed to scare her.

215
00:11:31,575 --> 00:11:33,099
Any chance you remember his name?

216
00:11:33,099 --> 00:11:35,469
Save us trying to match 
that story to the sender?

217
00:11:35,469 --> 00:11:36,983
Lo got a lot of letters.

218
00:11:36,983 --> 00:11:41,694
No. It's the stories that stick,  
not their names.

219
00:11:42,007 --> 00:11:44,069
Sorry.

220
